Myth: For eons, Ara sat at the Loom of Creation, where the world hung as a tapestry of flawless, silent crystal. Every river was a thread of motionless silver, every leaf a stitch of unmoving jade. It was a vision of absolute order, beautiful but dead in its perfection. Ara knew that for the world to truly exist, it must learn to tremble.

She gathered the stray, frayed ends of the universe—the wild, untamed energies that refused to be smooth. Twisting these chaotic fibers together, she spun the Thread of Discord. It was rough, dark, and vibrated with a low, humming energy. With a steady hand, she wove this rugged line right through the center of her pristine design.

The moment the Discord crossed the smooth warp and weft, the crystal tapestry shattered into soft movement. The friction of the rough thread against the smooth silk created the first spark of heat, birthing the sun. The vibration of the clash created the wind. The world was no longer a frozen picture but a moving, breathing entity, forever struggling to smooth out the rough thread Ara had hidden in its heart. That eternal struggle between order and the wild thread is what we call life.
